BRIEFING:
TRADES SHOULD EASE TODAY ALLOWING FOR SEA/LAND BREEZES TO DEVELOP ACROSS THE STATE. THIS AFTERNOON. TRADES SHOULD INCREASE TOMORROW WITH A COLD FRONT APPROACHING. A FEW SHRA MAY AFFECT WINDWARD AND MAUKA LOCATIONS THIS MORNING, OTHERWISE MOSTLY DRY WEATHER AND VFR CONDITIONS SHOULD PREVAIL. SHRA ASSOCIATED WITH THE COLD FRONT WILL BRING SOME REDUCED CIGS/VSBYS TO THE WESTERN ISLANDS LATE TONIGHT AND WEDNESDAY MORNING.
THREAT: SIGMET SIERRA SERIES FOR FCST SEV TURB NORTH OF ISLANDS BETWEEN FL200 AND FL410 MOVING EAST NORTH EAST.
